msgstr ""

#: includes/class-health-checks.php
msgid "PHP memory limit is below 64 MB. WordPress and many plugins need at least 64 MB to run reliably. Contact your host or increase `memory_limit` in php.ini or wp-config.php."
msgstr ""

#. translators: %d is the plugin count threshold integer
#: includes/class-health-checks.php
msgid "You have %d or more active plugins. While not a hard limit, a large number of plugins increases the risk of conflicts and slows down administration. Deactivate any plugins you are not actively using."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-health-checks.php
msgid "DISABLE_WP_CRON is enabled without evidence of an alternative cron job. WordPress scheduled tasks (updates, publishing, emails) will not run unless your server calls wp-cron.php on a schedule. Configure a server-side cron job to call `wp-cron.php?doing_wp_cron` at least once per minute."
msgstr ""

